got a rude shock when i opened my otah. just go elsewhere and buy la guys

Went early at 830am and got
1. Spicy fish head otah (just nice level of spicy, has actual bits of fish head inside)
2. Big otah (spicy and flavourful but the texture was not there)
3. Normal otah (shiok, nice level of spicy)
4. Not spicy otah (meh, wouldnâ€™t get it again)
Otah was flavourful, but overly salty and not warm. Also, too expensive at 80 cents a piece as it was almost paper thin.

I purchased the non-spicy otah and was taken aback by the price of 80 cents per piece. However, upon opening it for consumption, I discovered that it contained a disappointingly thin layer of fish meat. In comparison, otah I've bought from elsewhere has proven to be of better quality and cheaper. Additionally, the people at this place tend to be quite persistent in their attempts to upsell other products. Never gonna buy from them again.
